{"id":873367892,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"5 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1673103687,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"6 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/873367892/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"42.8 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int romanToInt(String s) {\n        HashMap<Character,Integer> map=new HashMap<>();\n        map.put('I',1);\n        map.put('V',5);\n        map.put('X',10);\n        map.put('L',50);\n        map.put('C',100);\n        map.put('D',500);\n        map.put('M',1000);\n        char[] ch=s.toCharArray();\n       \n       int j=0;\n       int ans=0;\n       while(j<ch.length-1){\n           if( map.get(ch[j]) < map.get(ch[j+1])){\n               ans+=map.get(ch[j+1])-map.get(ch[j]);\n               j+=2;\n           }else{\n               ans+=map.get(ch[j]);    \n               j++;\n           }\n        \n       }\n       if(j==ch.length-1) ans+=map.get(ch[j]);\n       return ans;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false}
